title: Harris Academy at Peckham
description:
Was formerly Warwick Park, changed it to The Academy at Peckham, and renamed it to Harris Academy at Peckham when the school received funding from Lord Harris of Peckham. 
Harris Academy at Peckham is a co-educational secondary school for 11-18 that had been awarded the academy status
112 Peckham Road, London SE15 5DZ
Tel: 020 77034417
Fax: 020 77034305

title: Camberwell Bus Garage
description: Large depot for London buses. Opened as bus depot in 1919. Not open to the public.

title: Site of Bermondsey Abbey
description: Here was one of the most important English monasteries.   The land was divided up for large houses and these were replaced with industrial premises and smaller houses.   Excavations have revealed parts of the plan.   The only visible evidence above ground is half of a gate hinge in Grange Walk, which formed the entrance to an outer enclosure of the abbey.

title: Bermondsey Spa Gardens
description: Created after World War II by demolition of several streets.   The original 18th Century Bermondsey Spa Gardens were nearby.

title: William Booth Memorial Training College
description:
The headquarters of The Salvation Army leadership and officer training in United Kingdom. The college officially opened in 1929 as a memorial of William Booth; it is Grade ll listed.

title: Michael Faraday Gardens
description: In the first years of the 20th century, slums were cleared to create Faraday Gardens. This was done by Octavia Hill. Named after scientist Michael Faraday. The Walworth Festival is held here in the middle of the summer.

title: Railway Sidings (Bakerloo Line)
description: The line's original depot and unusual in that although the depot is on the surface the line passes nearby in tunnel, connected by a short and sharply graded branch tunnel. -Wikipedia.
